items.preText: Arsalan: "The greatness of Shakib is highlighted by the fact that he would easily make it into this side or most other sides, either purely as a batsman or a bowler. Kallis, who was probably the greatest all-rounder ever would have found it difficult to break into the South African side purely as a bowler. A similar case could be argued for England's Ben Stokes who may not make it to the England XI purely on his bowling."
